  "doc_id": "51415",
  "text": "A total of 4981 ESTs generated from mRNA sequencing of E. distachya were retrieved from the National Center for Biotechnology Information (NCBI) Expressed Sequence Tags database (dbEST) (accessed by searching with \"(Ephedra) AND \"Ephedra distachya\"[porgn:__txid3389]\"). Microsatellites with a minimum repeat number of five were detected for 324 ESTs with a minimum length of 200 bp. We obtained 203 unique EST-SSR loci by an allagainst-all BLAST analysis and successfully designed primers for 171 unique EST-SSR loci. All bioinformatic operations were performed using the microsatellite detection and development pipeline QDD version 3.1 [CITATION_1] . Finally, we selected 88 di-or trinucleotide loci with at least five repeats for further evaluation.",
